Sorry to also chime in with what seems like bitching and moaning but the audio is REALLY BAD. It isn't the bad audio.... the movie was free to me so what the hell right..... WHY was it labeled as 8 Channel.!!!!!!! it is mono and the treble is maxed thru the roof!!!!! I am happy to have this copy, the video is PERFECT!!!! honestly, The audio is so bad it makes it hard to watch.  I saw a CAM version of this a month or so ago and it had bad Audio and Video. If I didn't already know the story from watching the CAM version, I would probably sit through the entire film but I will save it and see if a version with great audio comes around and then splice the good audio into this file. I can't truely complain for it is a free deal but like I said PLEASE, when you post a file just be straight forward about what it is that is being put out here. I don't think that is a big deal to ask as much??? right??? ANYWAY.... I'll check back later to see if a better audio vs comes along.

At first, I thought it was the movie because you are seeing the world through a cheap hand held video camera.... but after that part was done and the story was now supposed be being seen as a half million dollar PanaVision motion picture camera would see the world but the rest of the movie looks like the hand held video camera part never ends. (If anyone saw CLOVERDALE, they know what I mean...
